02/25/2025,748.2855(b) - Emergency Behavior Intervention,Emergency Behavior Intervention,No,03/11/2025,03/21/2025,N:Emergency Behavior Intervention,Medium High,Yes,"A restraint report dated February 22, 2025 at 11:15 AM was not reviewed within the 72-hour timeframe which should've been by February 25, 2025 at 11:15 AM.  The supervisor date and time was blank.","Operation provided the training roster for Documentation completed on March 21, 2025. 
Operation's mandatory training was rescheduled to March 21, 2025 due to children in care being on Spring Break.
The operation provided the following response on March 3, 2025:
Standard 748.311/748.2855(b)-Serious Incident Documentation/EBI Documentation-the serious incident report has been revised and corrected to include required information.  Amazing Touch Care Home has only one serious incident report that staff must complete.   This process was completed by Program Administrator, Lecia Hurst to ensure accurate and complete documentation.   The Program Administrator/ and or Program Designee will review all serious incident reports and restraint reports within 24 hours after the serious incident has occurred.  All staff are required to complete and sign/date serious incidents, and restraint reports before their assigned shift is complete.   The reports will be reviewed for true and accurate information by Program Administrator, Lecia Hurst or Program Designee within 24 hours.  All serious incidents and restraint reports will be signed by Program Administrator/Designee within 24 hours.   
Mandatory Documentation training has been scheduled for all staff on March 14, 2025.  
"
